  "decision_conditions": [
    "CONDITION: Notwithstanding the plans hereby approved the roof extension shall be reduced in length so that it is set back from the front, Hilldrop Road, parapet by no less than 2 metres. The extension shall be carried out strictly in accordance with the revised set back unless detailed evidence (that may include an on site mock up), is submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority which demonstrates that a roof extension of a lesser set back would not be visible from immediate or long views.\r\n\r\nREASON: To ensure that the extension is not visible from Hilldrop Road streetscene in immediate or long views, the amendment ensures compliance with policy CS9 of the Core Strategy 2011, policies D4, D11 and D25 of the UDP 2002, Hillmarton Conservation Area Guidelines, and PPS5."
